quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  68,1,"Nun, (The is the name of a letter of the Arabic alphabet, and only Allah knows its meaning here) and (by) the pen and what they inscribe"
  68,2,"In no way are you, by the favor of your Lord, a madman"
  68,3,And surely you will have indeed a reward bountifully unfailing
  68,4,And surely you are indeed of a magnificent character
  68,5,"So you will behold, and they will behold"
  68,6,"Whichever of you is the demented (The is the name of a letter of the Arabic alphabet, and only Allah knows its meaning here)"
  68,7,"Surely your Lord, He, Ever He, knows best the ones who have erred away from His way, and He Ever He, knows best the right-guided ones"
  68,8,So do not obey the beliers
  68,9,"They would like (if) you would dissimulate, then they would dissimulate"
  68,10,"And do not obey every most contemptible (person), constantly swearing"
  68,11,"Constantly slandering, ever-walking about with detraction"
  68,12,"Constant preventer of charity, constantly-vicious transgressor"
  68,13,"Coarse-grained, and of spurious parentage after all (Literally: after that)"
  68,14,"For that he has (Literally: for that he owns) wealth and sons"
  68,15,"When Our ayat (Verses, signs) are recited to him, he says, \"Myths of the earliest (people)"
  68,16,We will (brand) him markedly upon the snout
  68,17,"Surely We have tried them as We tried the companions (i.e., owners) of the garden, as they swore that indeed they would definitely wrest away (i.e., gather all) (its fruits) in the (early) morning"
  68,18,And made no exception (for the Will of Allah)
  68,19,"Then a (destructive) visitation from your Lord visited (Literally: went around it) it while they were sleeping"
  68,20,So (in the morning) it became as if it were a garden wrested away
  68,21,Then in the (early) morning they called out to one another
  68,22,"(Saying), \"Go forth early upon your tillage, in case you would wrest away (the fruit)"
  68,23,"So they went off, speaking together in hushed voices"
  68,24,"(Saying), \"Definitely no indigent person shall enter it today against you"
  68,25,"And they went forth early, determined on interdiction"
  68,26,"Then, as soon as they saw it, they said, \"Surely we are indeed erring (people)"
  68,27,"No indeed, (but) we are dispossessed"
  68,28,"Said the most moderate of them, \"Did I not say to you: Had you only extolled (Him)"
  68,29,"They said, All Extolment be to our Lord! Surely we were unjust"
  68,30,"Then some of them came forward to others, blaming each other"
  68,31,"They said, \"O woe to us! Surely we were inordinate"
  68,32,"It may be that our Lord will give us in exchange a more charitable (i.e., better) one than it; surely to our Lord are we desirous (of His Grace)"
  68,33,"Thus was the torment; and the torment of the Hereafter is indeed greater, if they did know"